race.comment: Forgive the last run of EMPHATIC BEL (7) who was run off her legs over 800m at Narromine. Beaten just half a length two runs ago over this distance at Dubbo in a BM66 which is good form for a race like this. Perfectly drawn to bounce back to form. ZOUCHASE (1) shouldered 62.5kgs and bolted in at Charleville last time out over 1100m. This is a tougher race but he goes fast and should give a good account. The speedy BRUMMAGEN (4) improved sharply last start at Narromine when second-up from a spell. Draws a better gate this time and should be in the finish again. Market watch on the sparingly raced mare CROOK (5) who is back from a 29-week spell.
